headline: Fastenal (NasdaqGS:FAST) Announces Two-for-One Stock Split to Increase Share Authorization
summary: Fastenal (NasdaqGS:FAST) recently approved a two-for-one stock split, increasing authorized shares, coinciding with a 6% share price rise last quarter. This action might have influenced investor sentiment, aligning with broader market gains fueled by upbeat earnings reports and tariff optimism. Fastenal's earnings disclosure of stable EPS and minor sales upswing indicates steady performance amidst macroeconomic uncertainty. Executive transitions, like Sheryl A. headline: FAST Q1 Earnings Call: Management Addresses Tariffs, Supply Chain, and Digital Strategy
summary: Industrial supplier Fastenal (NASDAQ:FAST) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales up 3.4% year on year to $1.96 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.52 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.
